    "actor": "https://uofa.net/morrison/actor/credibility-panel",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors appropriately scoped out per ASME V&V 40 Table 3 at MRL 2. Output comparison confirms RH < 1 at all five CPB operating points. The hemolysis prediction methodology is consistent with approaches described in the computational hemolysis literature, including the power-law stress-based framework detailed in the methodological review at https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ymeth.2024.03.003, which provides updated parameter estimates for the Giersiepen-Wurzinger model used in this assessment. Discretization error (GCI 1.8%) and experimental agreement (mean error 6.2%) provide sufficient confidence for the Class II CPB tolerance decision. Credibility package accepted for regulatory submission.",
